  "intent": "Perform a comprehensive lean review of the Codex Signum system. (1) Revalidate all pattern SIPOCs against current implementation AND against the Codex axioms — do not assume implementation is correct where it diverges from the maps. (2) Revalidate all 10 NFRs. (3) Update the gap analysis with new gaps discovered during M-7B and M-8A. (4) Rebuild the dependency matrix without Observer or Sentinel. (5) Map the complete value stream from user intent to committed output and identify waste using Lean Six Sigma methodology — apply Cp/Cpk, percent-complete-and-accurate, RTY, PCE, common-cause vs special-cause variation, MSA, and 5 Whys. (6) Define functional requirements for the Codex-native topology refactor — pipeline output as graph nodes, multi-dimensional Thompson learning, self-referential axiom review, jidoka/Andon-cord hallucination detection (FR-12 through FR-15), pre-flight auth validation (FR-9), file context injection at DISPATCH (FR-10), directory metadata at DECOMPOSE (FR-11). (7) Define non-functional requirements for the refactor. (8) Establish baseline measurements of current capabilities from M-7B and M-8A runs. (9) Apply axioms with scope awareness: operational scope (axioms constrain running system) vs review scope (the review evaluates whether the foundation is correct). Do not use Semantic Stability to block foundational recommendations — cite substantive reasons. Reference the lean process maps (docs/lean/codex-signum-lean-process-maps-v2.md), the axiom audit (docs/lean/lean-process-maps-audit.md), the Phase 2-3 validation (docs/validation/phase-2-3-axiom-validation.md), the OpEx research paper (docs/research/Codex_Signum_Stands_on_the_Shoulders_of_Operational_Excellence_Giants.md), M-8A consolidated findings (docs/pipeline-output/2026-03-01T08-19-52/), and the Codex v3.0 spec (docs/specs/01_codex-signum-v3_0.md).",
